 done (98.5%).\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — which stories were attempted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize and analyze all issues from the session log:\n   - The critical issue is ralph spawning 11 consecutive no-op sessions burning API credits\n   - 14-4-observability-backend-choice has been stuck for many sessions\n3. **What went well** — sprint is 98.5% complete\n4. **What went wrong** — ralph loop not terminating on NO_WORK\n5. **Lessons learned** — need circuit breaker for consecutive no-ops\n6. **Action items** — concrete next steps\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-25.md where the date is 2026-03-25.\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"a62d321b6495a2283","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Session 17 retrospective written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-25.md`.\n\nKey findings:\n\n- **11 consecutive NO_WORK sessions** (7-17) burned API credits with zero productive output\n- **Root cause:** Ralph's circuit breaker monitors file changes, not work outcomes. Since ralph writes its own state files every session, the breaker never trips.\n- **Sprint is 98.5% complete** (65/66 stories). The sole remaining story (14-4-observability-backend-choice) is retry-exhausted and requires Docker access that's unavailable in ralph's non-interactive session.\n- **P0 action items:** Add consecutive no-op counter (terminate after 3), fix circuit breaker to check story status transitions instead of file modifications."}],"totalDurationMs":80099,"totalTokens":19522,"totalToolUseCount":7,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2023,"cache_read_input_tokens":17294,"out